parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission and shifting system can cause the vehicle to stall, hesitate, or lunge forward, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or stalls when shifting gears
the shifter lights do not turn on
the vehicle lunges forward without input from the driver
and the transmission makes abnormal noises.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch and hydraulic system can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
and the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.
